From: PiDVD <pidvd@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] drm/vc4: field-lock vblank sequence parity on interlaced
 scanout

On interlaced modes the PV raises a vblank interrupt per FIELD, but
nothing in the DRM UAPI tells userspace which field a vblank or flip
event refers to, making field-accurate presentation (e.g. a DVD player
feeding a CRT) a matter of guesswork.

The HVS fifo frame counter (SCALER_DISPSTAT1/2 FRCNTx) increments per
field and is the hardware's authoritative field identity — the driver
already consults it for the scanout-position field offset. Keep the
software vblank counter's parity locked to it: if they disagree after a
vblank is handled, account one extra vblank to resynchronize.

Userspace can then derive absolute field identity from the sequence
number of any vblank wait or page-flip event (constant parity <-> field
mapping). Because the check runs on every vblank interrupt, a missed
interrupt cannot silently invert the mapping; it heals on the next tick.

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_crtc.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/vc4/vc4_crtc.c
@@ -871,6 +871,7 @@
 {
 	struct drm_encoder *encoder = vc4_get_crtc_encoder(&crtc->base, crtc->base.state);
 	struct vc4_encoder *vc4_encoder = to_vc4_encoder(encoder);
+	struct vc4_dev *vc4 = to_vc4_dev(crtc->base.dev);
 
 	crtc->t_vblank = ktime_get();
 
@@ -878,6 +879,27 @@
 		vc4_encoder->vblank(encoder);
 
 	drm_crtc_handle_vblank(&crtc->base);
+
+	/*
+	 * Field-lock the vblank sequence on interlaced scanout: the HVS
+	 * fifo frame counter increments per field, so its parity is the
+	 * hardware's field identity. Keeping the software vblank
+	 * counter's parity equal to it lets userspace read absolute
+	 * field identity from any event's sequence number, and a missed
+	 * interrupt self-heals here instead of silently inverting field
+	 * order.
+	 */
+	if (crtc->base.state &&
+	    (crtc->base.state->adjusted_mode.flags & DRM_MODE_FLAG_INTERLACE) &&
+	    vc4->hvs) {
+		u64 seq = drm_crtc_vblank_count(&crtc->base);
+		u8 frame = vc4_hvs_get_fifo_frame_count(vc4->hvs,
+						crtc->current_hvs_channel);
+
+		if ((seq ^ frame) & 1)
+			drm_crtc_handle_vblank(&crtc->base);
+	}
+
 	vc4_crtc_handle_page_flip(crtc);
 }
 
